#
# Validated configuration (do not change without re-validation):
#   dual physical DGX Spark, TP=2 multiprocessing, one rank per node, NET/IB over RoCE,
#   MTP n=1, FULL_DECODE_ONLY, capture size [2] (one target/verify graph per rank,
#   draft path EAGER), FlashMLA, EP off, prefix cache off, parser off, tool parser off,
#   B12X off, Ray off, fixed KV 2 GiB, KV dtype fp8, max-model-len 8192, max-seqs 1,
#   max-batched-tokens 2048, GPU mem util 0.87, concurrency 1 (validated ONLY at 1),
#   async scheduler auto-enabled, VLLM_USE_BREAKABLE_CUDAGRAPH=0.
#
# Required two-node topology: spark01 = head/rank0 (10.10.10.1), spark02 = worker/rank1
#   (10.10.10.2), HCA rocep1s0f0 port 1 GID index 3. Single-node TP=1 is IMPOSSIBLE for
#   the official 46-shard checkpoint on a single GB10.
#
# Operational prerequisites (NOT performed by this preset — see provenance doc):
#   1. Clean boot before every full model load. GB10 UMA retains ~37-40 GiB after a
#      container stop; if MemAvailable < 110 GiB due to UVM retention, reboot BOTH nodes
#      exactly once. Automatic reboot is NOT part of this preset.
#   2. Clear ONLY the dedicated vLLM compilation cache (./.cache/vllm) on BOTH nodes
#      before start (guards the SM121 stale-compile-cache garble).
#   3. Keep attention backend = default FlashMLA sparse-MLA (do NOT switch to FlashInfer
#      MLA). Keep VLLM_USE_BREAKABLE_CUDAGRAPH=0.
#
# Expected memory behaviour (validated): clean boot ~117-118 GiB MemAvailable/node;
#   weight load ~73.82 GiB/rank; init swap ~2-3 GiB then flat; steady-state minimum
#   ~30-32 GiB MemAvailable; no sustained paging during measured inference; post-stop
#   UVM retention ~37-40 GiB MemAvailable (reboot required before next full load).
#   Negative graph-memory log values (e.g. "-0.01 GiB") are allocator accounting noise.
#
# Expected throughput (validated operational range, API-visible decode; do NOT promise
#   a fixed 39 t/s floor): d0 ~38.9-40.2 t/s, d4096 ~37.1-39.8 t/s. Normal-workload
#   speculative acceptance ~80-90% (4h global 86.89%, cold-repro normal 87.63%).
#
# Rollback references (see provenance doc for full procedure):
